DIABOLIC: Pure, absolute evil without restraint

Diabolic is pure, absolute evil.  A Diabolic character has no moral
code, no mercy, no remorse.  They kill for fun, destroy for pleasure,
and take what they want without hesitation.  They are the monsters that
good-aligned characters exist to stop.

A Diabolic character might lie, torture, murder, and betray without a
second thought.  They are unpredictable in their cruelty, bound by
nothing.  They might honor a bargain today and slaughter the other
party tomorrow because they felt like it.  Life, suffering, and death
are all equally entertaining to them.

GUIDELINES
  - No moral restraint whatsoever
  - Will lie, betray, torture, and kill for profit, entertainment, or
    convenience
  - Makes and breaks promises at whim; has no concept of personal honor
  - Actively enjoys causing suffering when the opportunity is safe
  - May work with others but will turn on them without warning
  - Attacks the weak as readily as the strong; no line they will not
    cross

Diabolic characters are the great evils of Rifts Earth: the Splugorth
Slaughter Host commander who levels cities for sport, the serial killer
who haunts the ruins, the demon lord who views all of humanity as prey.
Playing a Diabolic character requires significant narrative context:
the world is already full of monsters, and adding one to the party is a
serious challenge for any group.

Other characters of all alignments view Diabolic characters as threats
to be eliminated.  Even Miscreants and Aberrants may refuse to work
with someone they cannot predict or control.

